com.interpss.core.aclf

Interface BaseAclfBus<TGen extends AclfGen,TLoad extends AclfLoad>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Bus, com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ExtensionElement, IAclfBus, IAclfBusAdaptation, IAclfBusAdjustment, IAclfBusFunc, IAclfBusZeroZFunc, NameTag, NetworkedElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    AclfBus, AcscBus, BaseAcscBus<TGen,TLoad>, BaseDStabBus<TGen,TLoad>, DStabBus, OpfBus, SEBus, Static3PBus
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AclfBusImpl, AcscBusImpl, BaseAclfBusImpl, BaseAcscBusImpl, BaseDStabBusImpl, DStabBusImpl, OpfBusImpl, SEBusImpl, Static3PBusImpl

    public interface BaseAclfBus<TGen extends AclfGen,TLoad extends AclfLoad>
extends Bus, IAclfBus, IAclfBusFunc, IAclfBusZeroZFunc, IAclfBusAdaptation, IAclfBusAdjustment
    A representation of the model object 'Bus'. AclfBus class is for storing bus information for AC loadflow analysis. AclfBus could be extended using IAclfBus or ICustomLoad interface.

    The following features are supported:

    • Gen Code
    • Load Code
    • Voltage Mag
    • Voltage Ang
    • Desired Volt Mag
    • Desired Volt Ang
    • Gen P
    • Gen Q
    • Load P
    • Load Q
    • Shunt Y
    • Exp Load P
    • Exp Load Q
    • QGen Limit
    • PGen Limit
    • VLimit
    • External Power Into Net
    • Contribute Gen List
    • Contribute Load List
    • Compensator List
    • Switched Shunt List
    • Function Load
    • Bus Control
    • Remote QControl Group
    See Also:
    AclfPackage.getBaseAclfBus()

      • getExternalPowerIntoNet

        org.apache.commons.math3.complex.Complex getExternalPowerIntoNet()
        Returns the value of the 'External Power Into Net' attribute. The default value is "". Loadflow commonly has an inter-loop and an out-loop calculation. It is used to represent the external or out-loop power at the bus, into the network as the positive direction.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'External Power Into Net' attribute.
        See Also:
        setExternalPowerIntoNet(Complex), AclfPackage.getBaseAclfBus_ExternalPowerIntoNet()

      • mismatch

        org.apache.commons.math3.complex.Complex mismatch(AclfMethodType lfMethod)
        Calculate bus mismatch = specified - calculated, with into network direction as the positive direction, in pu. When method = QA, mismatch = (dP + jdQ) for all bus types for QA testing purpose.
        Parameters:
        lfMethod - the loadflow method to be used for the mismatch calculation. Valid options (NR, PQ, QA).

      • b11ii

        double b11ii()
        Calculate bus B11ii, in pu.
        1) phase shifter not represented;
        2) 'I', 'Z' load not represented
        3) shunt Y not represented

      • b1ii

        double b1ii()
        Calculate bus B1ii, in pu
        1) shunt susceptance not represented
        2) off-nominal taps not represented
        3) 'I', 'Z' load not represented
        4) grounded branch not represented
        5) shunt Y not represented

      • acCurrentIntoNet

        org.apache.commons.math3.complex.Complex acCurrentIntoNet()

      • powerIntoNet

        org.apache.commons.math3.complex.Complex powerIntoNet()
        Calculate the power into the network, which is the product of voltage and the conjugate of the current into the network, plus the external power into the network.
